rComments: Professor Walton is one of the best professors Ive had at U of T. She is easily accessible outside of class and is a huge help with essays. She cares about her students and the subject material- a perfect combination.

Amazing Prof and a lovely human being. Lectures were clear, organized and insightful, gave great feedback on essays, encouraged class discussions but never shot down student's ideas, was always very respectful to students and their opinions. A very kind, approachable person, and very intelligent! Plus made the course content super interesting.

The way she balances lecture with discussion is really innovative and useful. Her approach to medieval text feels very contemporary and I learned a lot, not just about the material, but about different ways to read and interpret texts. I highly recommend taking Walton's class.
